Package: tinypedigree
Title: Plots Simple Pedigree Diagrams
Version: 0.0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Kim", "Bridges", , "kim.bridges@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A wrapper for kinship2 functions that let you build pedigree
    diagrams using one or two data files as input. You control the
    appearance of the color and fill of the symbol with table values.
    A slash across the symbol is also available. The second data table
    is used, if necessary, identifying married couples who have no children.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
Imports: 
    dplyr,
    kinship2
Suggests: 
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
